- n. <</>id. +. (šaiva.)
- A condition of the soul in its uplifted state when it becomes one with the Divine Grace;  and is conscious of the distinction of āturu;  āṉam  and  ēyam ;  one of five  cuttāvattai ;  q.v. ;
